<collectionCode id="ED1A428DE436FFFF9447FD7AFE2FFD01" box="[330,384,640,666]" country="Sri Lanka" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13944" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13944" name="Royal Botanic Gardens" pageId="9" pageNumber="89" type="Herbarium">PDA</collectionCode>
reaching 
<quantity id="4CF377ADE436FFFF94E3FD7AFDC9FD00" box="[494,614,640,667]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="89" unit="mm" value="21.0" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="20.0">20–22 mm</quantity>
diam. after 10 days at 25 °C, cottony, low convex, margin entire to slightly undulated, white. Reverse white to pale yellow. No growth at 5 °C nor at 30 °C.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4DA48E436FFFF95B0FD32FB23FC9D" blockId="9.[136,1452,496,919]" pageId="9" pageNumber="89">
Colonies on MEA reaching 
<quantity id="4CF377ADE436FFFF94F6FD32FDDAFD78" box="[507,629,712,739]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="9" pageNumber="89" unit="mm" value="23.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="21.0">21–25 mm</quantity>
diam. after 10 days at 25 °C, cottony, low convex to raise with concave edge, margin entire, white. Reverse pale yellow to orangey. No growth at 5 °C nor at 30 °C.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4DA48E436FFFF95B0FCEAFD49FC0D" blockId="9.[136,1452,496,919]" pageId="9" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE436FFFF95B0FCEAFEC9FCB1" box="[189,358,784,810]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="89">Asexual morph</emphasis>
: Hyphae hyaline and smooth-walled, Phialides 16–31 × 0.9–1.2 µm, mostly solitary, arising from prostrate hyphae, straight to slightly curved, tapering to the apex. 
<emphasis id="B97F065AE436FFFF9651FCCEFC19FCD5" box="[860,950,820,846]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="89">Conidia</emphasis>
1-celled, smooth-walled, variable in size and shape, Microconidia 1.8–3 × 0.9–1.5 µm, adhering in globose slimy heads, subglobose to ellipsoidal. Macroconidia 5–8 × 1–1.6 µm, fusiform. Octahedral crystals absent.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF748AC0E436FFFF9585F8E7FDB5F8A9" box="[136,538,1821,1843]" pageId="9" pageNumber="89" startId="9.[136,229,1821,1843]">
<paragraph id="8BB4DA48E436FFFF9585F8E7FDB5F8A9" blockId="9.[136,1452,1821,1951]" box="[136,538,1821,1843]" pageId="9" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE436FFFF9585F8E7FF52F8A9" bold="true" box="[136,253,1821,1843]" pageId="9" pageNumber="89">FIGURE 5.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE436FFFF940EF8E7FDB5F8A9" authorityName="J. Leplat" authorityYear="2021" box="[259,538,1821,1842]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Simplicillium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="9" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pech-merlensis">Simplicillium pech-merlensis</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BB4DA48E436FFFF9585F8BBFD7AF804" blockId="9.[136,1452,1821,1951]" pageId="9" pageNumber="89">
a–b. Upper and reverse views of the culture on MEA (10 d at 25 °C). c–d. Upper and reverse views of the culture on 
<collectionCode id="ED1A428DE436FFFF9007F8B8FA96F8CC" box="[1290,1337,1858,1879]" country="Sri Lanka" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13944" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13944" name="Royal Botanic Gardens" pageId="9" pageNumber="89" type="Herbarium">PDA</collectionCode>
(10 d at 25 °C). e–f. Solitary phialides and microconidia that adhere to each other to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE436FFFF964FF89FFC6DF8E0" box="[834,962,1893,1915]" form="globose" pageId="9" pageNumber="89" rank="form">form globose</taxonomicName>
slimy heads. g. Microconidia and macroconidia. h. Solitary phialide and macroconidia. Scale bars: e–h = 10 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4DA48E436FFFF95B0F834FA04F873" blockId="9.[136,1451,1998,2060]" box="[189,1451,1998,2024]" pageId="9" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE436FFFF95B0F834FDC8F873" box="[189,615,1998,2024]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="89">
Notes:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE436FFFF942CF834FDC8F873" authorityName="J. Leplat" authorityYear="2021" box="[289,615,1998,2024]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Simplicillium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="9" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pech-merlensis">Simplicillium pech-merlensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
seems morphologically close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE436FFFF96D1F834FA08F873" authority="Z. F. Zhang, F. Liu &amp; L. Cai" authorityName="Z. F. Zhang, F. Liu &amp; L. Cai" authorityYear="2017" box="[988,1447,1998,2024]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Simplicillium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="9" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="calcicola">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE436FFFF96D1F834FBCFF873" box="[988,1120,1998,2024]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="89">S. calcicola</emphasis>
Z.F. Zhang, F. Liu &amp; L. Cai
</taxonomicName>
,
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4DA48E436FFFC9585F808FE64FE0B" blockId="9.[136,1451,1998,2060]" lastBlockId="10.[136,1452,158,401]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="90" pageId="9" pageNumber="89">
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE436FFFF9585F808FE49F797" authority="Z. F. Zhang &amp; L. Cai" authorityName="Z. F. Zhang &amp; L. Cai" authorityYear="2020" box="[136,486,2034,2060]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Simplicillium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="9" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="album">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE436FFFF9585F808FF42F797" box="[136,237,2034,2060]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="89">S. album</emphasis>
Z.F. Zhang &amp; L. Cai
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE436FFFF972FF808FD10F797" box="[546,703,2034,2060]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Simplicillium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="9" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="lamellicola">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE436FFFF972FF808FD10F797" box="[546,703,2034,2060]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="89">S. lamellicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE436FFFF9661F808FB9BF797" authorityName="J. Leplat" authorityYear="2021" box="[876,1076,2034,2060]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Simplicillium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="9" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pech-merlensis">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE436FFFF9661F808FB9BF797" box="[876,1076,2034,2060]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="89">S. pech-merlensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE436FFFF9148F808FB64F797" authorityName="Z. F. Zhang, F. Liu &amp; L. Cai" authorityYear="2017" box="[1093,1227,2034,2060]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Simplicillium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="9" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="calcicola">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE436FFFF9148F808FB64F797" box="[1093,1227,2034,2060]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="89">S. calcicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE436FFFF900BF808FAC4F797" authorityName="Z. F. Zhang &amp; L. Cai" authorityYear="2020" box="[1286,1387,2034,2060]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Simplicillium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="9" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="album">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE436FFFF900BF808FAC4F797" box="[1286,1387,2034,2060]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="89">S. album</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were isolated from the same habitat, i.e. karst cave. While 
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE435FFFC97D9FF65FC35FF23" authorityName="J. Leplat" authorityYear="2021" box="[724,922,158,185]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Simplicillium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pech-merlensis">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE435FFFC97D9FF65FC35FF23" box="[724,922,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="90">S. pech-merlensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was isolated from the cave air, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE435FFFC91F5FF65FAD5FF23" authorityName="Z. F. Zhang, F. Liu &amp; L. Cai" authorityYear="2017" box="[1272,1402,158,185]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Simplicillium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="calcicola">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE435FFFC91F5FF65FAD5FF23" box="[1272,1402,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="90">S. calcicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was isolated from the limestone (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9AA7B9E435FFFC94C2FF38FD32FF47" author="Zhang, Z. &amp; Liu, F. &amp; Zhou, X. &amp; Liu, X. &amp; Liu, S. &amp; Cai, L." box="[463,669,194,220]" pageId="10" pageNumber="90" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref10778" refString="Zhang, Z., Liu, F., Zhou, X., Liu, X., Liu, S. &amp; Cai, L. (2017) Culturable mycobiota from Karst caves in China, with descriptions of 20 new species. Persoonia: Molecular Phylogeny and Evolution of Fungi 39: 1 - 31. https: // doi. org / 10.3767 / persoonia. 2017.39.01" type="journal article" year="2017">
Zhang 
<emphasis id="B97F065AE435FFFC972CFF39FDF5FF47" box="[545,602,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="90">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE435FFFC97D3FF39FCEEFF47" authorityName="Z. F. Zhang &amp; L. Cai" authorityYear="2020" box="[734,833,194,221]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Simplicillium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="album">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE435FFFC97D3FF39FCEEFF47" box="[734,833,194,221]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="90">S. album</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was isolated from the soil (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9AA7B9E435FFFC918DFF38FAF0FF46" author="Zhang, Z. - F. &amp; Zhou, S. - Y. &amp; Eurwilaichitr, L. &amp; Ingsriswang, S. &amp; Raza, M. &amp; Chen, Q. &amp; Zhao, P. &amp; Liu, F. &amp; Cai, L." box="[1152,1375,194,221]" pageId="10" pageNumber="90" refId="ref10688" refString="Zhang, Z. - F., Zhou, S. - Y., Eurwilaichitr, L., Ingsriswang, S., Raza, M., Chen, Q., Zhao, P., Liu, F. &amp; Cai, L. (2020 b) Culturable mycobiota from Karst caves in China II, with descriptions of 33 new species. Fungal Diversity. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13225 - 020 - 00453 - 7" type="book" year="2020">
Zhang 
<emphasis id="B97F065AE435FFFC91DFFF39FAA3FF47" box="[1234,1292,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="90">et al.</emphasis>
2020b
</bibRefCitation>
). Each species produces both microconidia and macroconidia. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE435FFFC97F8FF1CFBA0FE9B" box="[757,1039,230,256]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Simplicillium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="lamellicola">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE435FFFC97F8FF1CFBA0FE9B" box="[757,1039,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="90">Simplicillium lamellicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from the three other species by the production of octahedral crystals. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE435FFFC97A6FEF0FC22FEBF" authorityName="Z. F. Zhang &amp; L. Cai" authorityYear="2020" box="[683,909,266,292]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Simplicillium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="album">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE435FFFC97A6FEF0FC22FEBF" box="[683,909,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="90">Simplicillium album</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
produces larger macroconidia (8.0–11.0 (–13.0) × 2.0–3.5 μm) than 
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE435FFFC946FFED5FD87FED3" authorityName="J. Leplat" authorityYear="2021" box="[354,552,302,329]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Simplicillium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pech-merlensis">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE435FFFC946FFED5FD87FED3" box="[354,552,302,329]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="90">S. pech-merlensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(5–8 × 1–1.6 µm) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE435FFFC9628FED5FC08FED3" authorityName="Z. F. Zhang, F. Liu &amp; L. Cai" authorityYear="2017" box="[805,935,302,329]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Simplicillium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="calcicola">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE435FFFC9628FED5FC08FED3" box="[805,935,302,329]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="90">S. calcicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(4.5–8.0 × 1.0–2.0 μm). Finally, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE435FFFC901BFED4FE9DFEF7" authorityName="J. Leplat" authorityYear="2021" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Simplicillium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pech-merlensis">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE435FFFC901BFED4FE9DFEF7" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="90">Simplicillium pech-merlensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows slower in culture media (
<quantity id="4CF377ADE435FFFC9793FEA8FCB6FEF6" box="[670,793,338,365]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="90" unit="mm" value="21.0" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="20.0">20–22 mm</quantity>
diam after 10 days on 
<collectionCode id="ED1A428DE435FFFC9110FEA8FBF8FEF7" box="[1053,1111,338,364]" country="Sri Lanka" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13944" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13944" name="Royal Botanic Gardens" pageId="10" pageNumber="90" type="Herbarium">PDA</collectionCode>
) than 
<taxonomicName id="4C0BA1CBE435FFFC9193FEA9FA8DFEF7" authorityName="Z. F. Zhang, F. Liu &amp; L. Cai" authorityYear="2017" box="[1182,1314,338,365]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Simplicillium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="calcicola">
<emphasis id="B97F065AE435FFFC9193FEA9FA8DFEF7" box="[1182,1314,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="90">S. calcicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity id="4CF377ADE435FFFC903CFEA8FA03FEF6" box="[1329,1452,338,365]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="3.4" pageId="10" pageNumber="90" unit="mm" value="36.0" valueMax="38.0" valueMin="34.0">34–38 mm</quantity>
diam after 10 days on 
<collectionCode id="ED1A428DE435FFFC948FFE8CFE10FE0B" box="[386,447,374,400]" country="Sri Lanka" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13944" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13944" name="Royal Botanic Gardens" pageId="10" pageNumber="90" type="Herbarium">PDA</collectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
